<br>
Group1-<br>
2 Tanks 56+ (Auto-Riposte is a MUST)<br>
1 Rogue 55+ (Double BS)<br>
1 Druid/Ranger Druids 53+/Rangers 55+<br>
1 Enchanter 54+ (Rune V and Clarity II are a must :)<br>
1 Cleric 55+ (Heroic Bond and Symbol are important)<br>
<br>
Group2-<br>
1 Monk 55+ (Void Dance and Whirlwind)<br>
1 Rogue 55+ (Double BS)<br>
1 Druid/Ranger Druids 53+/Rangers 55+<br>
1 Enchanter 54+ (Rune V and Clarity II are a must :)<br>
1 Tank 56+ (Auto-Riposte is a MUST)<br>
1 Cleric 55+ (Heroic Bond and Symbol again)<br>
<br>
Have Group1 buff and begin pulling to staging area.  The route you take (left or right at statue) isn't important.  But, I would make sure that if Group1 is pulling from left, Group2 doesn't go right, hehe.  Once Group1 is in staging, have Group2 buff up and move in.  Getting to staging is cake. <br>
 <br>
NOTE:  A Rogue needs to be in each group because the door to staging is locked.  The reasoning behind staggering the groups moving in is quite simple.  The hallways leading to staging are narrow and people get bunched up.  If your tanks can't get to you, you will die.<br>
<br>
Once both groups are in staging, designate which Druid/Ranger will do turn in.  Let both groups know to NOT attack until they see 'Venril Sathir' pop.<br>
<br>
Seat whomever you have designated as your turn in PC directly in front of the Remains and hail him.  You must do this or, he may wander.  Also, now is the time to ask your Enchanter to Rune V the turn in PC and the 2 main /assists.  Have the tanks clear the rooms to the sides and back of the turn in PC.  Once the tanks have cleared the room, have the tanks SIT on either side of the Remains.  Position the Rogues directly behind the Remains.  Clerics and Chanters, sit in back of the room.... out of AE Lifetap range.<br>
NOTE:  VS2 DOES Lifetap and he WILL cause agro with it unless the rooms are kept clear.<br>
<br>
I am assuming that at this point, both groups are buffed and FM.  But, just to be sure, have the group leaders ask, and /tell you GTG or not.  If they are ready, the turn in PC stands up (VERY IMPORTANT) and hails the remains and /ooc's &quot;Turn in 1 NOW!&quot;.  The 'Spirit of Sathir' will pop.  The turn in PC then hails the Spirit and /ooc's &quot;Turn in 2 NOW!&quot;.  VS2 pops immediately.  Ideally, the tanks who were sitting on either side of the Remains/Spirit will get agro.  VS2 quads for 300 and will AE Lifetap when low on health.  This is where the Monk Void Dance and Warrior Auto-Riposte are important.  If all goes well, this fight should be over in about 20 seconds.  If it takes longer, don't sweat it.  VS2 is a complete wimp.  In fact, anyone who has fought the full VS will probably die laughing at how easy he is.<br>
<br>
I hope this clears the air and, good luck to you all in completing your Epics!  Lord knows, I love mine :)<br>
<br>
/cheer<br>
